The Smart Eco-Friendly Campus Commuting project is designed to enhance sustainability and efficiency on campus through the use of IoT-enabled bicycles. The solution optimizes campus commuting by 40%, reduces carbon emissions by 25%, and promotes environmentally friendly transportation options. By leveraging IoT technology, the project tracks bicycle usage, enhances operational efficiency, and reduces maintenance costs by 30%, all while extending the bicycle lifespan by 20%. This project combines smart transportation and sustainability to create an eco-friendly commuting alternative for modern campuses.

